80 (C) Notwithstanding other provisions of law in this paragraph, if the contractor has
81 performed any emergency services, acknowledged by the homeowner in writing to be
82 necessary to prevent immediate damage to the premises, the contractor shall be entitled
83 to collect the reasonable amount due for the emergency services at the time they are
84 rendered. Any provision in a contract provided for in this paragraph that requires the
85 payment of any fee for any services except emergency services shall not be enforceable
86 against any homeowner who has canceled a contract under this paragraph.
87 (D) As used in this paragraph, the term 'natural disaster' means a flood, tornado,
88 hurricane, earthquake, or other occurrence for which a state of emergency is proclaimed
89 by the Governor."
90 SECTION 3.
91 Code Section 33-6-5 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to unfair methods
92 of competition and unfair or deceptive acts or practices, is amended by striking "and" at the
93 end of paragraph (13), striking the period at the end of paragraph (14) and inserting "; and"
94 in lieu thereof, and adding a new paragraph to read as follows:
