95 "(15) No insurer shall sell homeowner's insurance policies that allow for the assignment
96 of proceeds to a contractor within one year of a natural disaster which causes damage to
97 the insured's residential property. As used in this paragraph, the term 'residential
98 property' means real property used or occupied as the primary residence of a natural
99 person."
100 SECTION 4.
101 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
